OL,3,CStudy pinpoints 'critical time
OL,4,Cwindows' for illnesses that pose
OL,5,Cdementia risk
OL,7,FHowever, from 55 to 70 years of age,
OL,8,Fmental health conditions such as
OL,9,Fanxiety and depression, as well as
OL,10,Fconditions such as stroke, increased
OL,11,Fthe risk of dementia two-fold.
OL,13,FSana Suri, an associate professor and
OL,14,FOxford Brain Sciences senior fellow,
OL,15,Fsaid: "Although we knew that
OL,16,Fmultimorbidity increased the risk of
OL,17,Fdementia, it was unclear which
OL,18,Fcombinations of health conditions had
OL,19,Fthe most impact and in what sequence.
