OL,3,CStudy pinpoints 'critical time
OL,4,Cwindows' for illnesses that pose
OL,5,Cdementia risk
OL,7,F"This study has identified how
OL,8,Fspecific illnesses tend to co-exist
OL,9,Fwith each other, and also the critical
OL,10,Ftime windows in which they could pose
OL,11,Fthe greatest risk."
OL,13,FElsewhere, the study suggests people
OL,14,Fwho have conditions such as heart
OL,15,Fdisease and diabetes in middle age,
OL,16,Ffollowed later by conditions such as
OL,17,Fstroke and mental health disorders
OL,18,Fwere at the greatest risk of
OL,19,Fdeveloping dementia.
